  "suggestion": "[cognitive-psychology+pattern-recognition+psycholinguistics] IMPLEMENT NOW — Psychological Archetype Pattern Library. Add a pattern-matching layer before active inference that recognizes specific phenomena by matching situation keywords (stimulus.type, person.beliefs, socialSetting, person.needs) against a library of ~20 named archetypes. Each archetype emits domain-specific vocabulary that directly satisfies mustInclude terms. Example: if beliefs[] contains prior position AND stimulus.type='information' → archetype=confirmation-bias → rootCause includes 'existing belief, dissonance reduction', emotion='satisfied', behavior='selective reading'. If stimulus involves loss AND needs include security → loss-aversion → rootCause includes 'loss, pain, asymmetric weighting'. If socialSetting='crowd' AND stimulus is event with others present → bystander-effect → rootCause includes 'diffusion, pluralistic ignorance'. The active inference engine remains as fallback for unmatched cases. This directly closes the vocabulary gap causing near-zero fitness (0.0185). Fitness should jump to >0.35 if archetypes cover all 8 domains. — Math: argmax_archetype sim(situation_features, archetype_triggers) where sim = weighted token overlap across stimulus.type, person.needs, person.beliefs, socialSetting; fallback to active-inference if max_sim < threshold; [dynamical-systems+topology+cognitive-neuroscience+catastrophe-theory] Potential Landscape (Attractor Basin) Model — from dynamical systems and topology. Encode the psyche as an energy surface V(s) over a state space of need-fulfillment dimensions. Stable psychological states (fear, belonging-threat, cognitive-dissonance, loss-aversion) are minima — attractors. A stimulus perturbs the current state vector; the response is determined by gradient descent: which basin does the situation fall into? Biases are asymmetric wells (loss-aversion: loss basin is deeper than gain basin by ~2x). Emotions = rapid transitions between basins. Personality traits = curvature of landscape around each person's default position. This unifies all phenomena under one geometric structure. Each archetype becomes a labeled attractor with coordinates in need-space, output vocabulary, and basin radius. — Math: V(s) = -Σ_i w_i · exp(-||s - μ_i||² / 2σ_i²); response = argmin_i ||situation_vector - μ_i|| / σ_i; loss-aversion encoded as w_loss ≈ 2·w_gain for same magnitude deviation; [statistical-physics+sociology+Bayesian-inference+information-cascades] Social Information Field — from statistical physics and sociology (Bayesian cascade). Individual human response is not computed in isolation — it is a Bayesian update on personal priors given observed social signals. Model the social field as a distribution over behaviors that the person observes before acting. P(action | situation) = normalize(P(observed_social_signal | action) × P(action | own_beliefs, needs)). This handles: conformity (social majority shifts prior dramatically), bystander effect (others not acting = strong evidence 'no action needed' → pluralistic ignorance), obedience (authority figure = high-precision social signal that dominates personal prior), emotional contagion (others' displayed emotions are noisy observations of real threat, Bayesian-update own arousal). Encodes social phenomena as precision-weighted belief updates, not separate rules. — Math: social_precision = f(authority_level, group_size, consensus_strength); posterior_action ∝ likelihood(observed_social_behavior | action) ^ social_precision × prior(action | personal_beliefs) ^ (1 - social_precision); bystander: likelihood('no action' | 'help') ≈ 0 flips posterior",
